devdoc.details: Wrappers over Solidity's uintXX/intXX/bool casting operators with added overflow checks. Downcasting from uint256/int256 in Solidity does not revert on overflow. Using this library instead of the unchecked operations eliminates an entire class of bugs, so it's recommended to use it always.

 `a**(p-2)` is the modular multiplicative inverse of a in Fp.
